That, my friends is how I feel.
I can honestly say that I believe there is no worse feeling in the world that unrequited love.

I'm on vacation and all I can think about it how much I want to not be here.  

Not Arizona. I love it here.

I mean here, as in, within exsistence.

Oh, and I want to kill Shane (my brother's friend who came with us)

Looking forward too and dredding next week all at the same time

"doesn't she look pretty?"

"Always."

Who knew a boy could say just one word and it would make me this content. I realize it was only to be nice and because I was standing right there, but it was still nice to hear.

:)

Not to mention, Ry Todd is coming out! July 25th! I so totally can't wait to see him.

Things are finally feeling good again.  

Well, I'm off to collage some pictures or something.

Later Lovies!

It sucks losing a friend.

It sucks more realizing your best friend isn't your best friend anymore.

It sucks the most to realize that your old best friend barely qualifies as an acquaintance and she couldn't care less
Just in case you were wondering, life sucks...or at least, mine does
Always the one's that I can't have...

I haven't been this happy in a long time...and all because a boy called me..haha.

As happy as I am, I've never felt so dumb in my life either.  How could one or two phone calls make me so giddy?

being a girl is so weird sometimes...haha
Two phone calls in one day! wow!

I feel like you don't care.

I know that silly and that maybe you even feel the same way.

We keep saying that we need to make an effort and yet, I can't honestly remember the last time we talked for more than five minutes.

It makes me sad.

I am losing the closest friend I ever had and I feel like there isn't anything I can do about it.

:(

I love you. You are part of my family, but lately, that's not enough.

I feel like I'm drowning

and the harder I try to stay  afloat

the faster I fall
I am having a crappy feel sorry for myself day, and I hate it.

It was so nice to feel wanted again,

It just sucks that you were the one who made me feel that way.

Finals are the bane of my existence.

So, yea, the stress got to me early. I kind of had a breakdown which involved calling my mom and crying, then talking to my dad and crying more.  To the point were my dad was ready to come get me and bring me home.  haha. Way to go Stef.

I am better now.  I realized that I was putting so much pressure on myself to succeed that it was basically going to be impossible to do so.

So, now I am trying to take the rest of my three finals in stride...just breathe and relax...for those of you who know what a worrier I am, this is easier for me to say then to actually do.

I hope finals are going well for all my college friends!  Good Luck guys!

haha.

In other news, I fixed my computer all by myself! yay! The co-op was like "it will be three days before we can even look at it" so I took matters into my own hands and it worked for once! yay!!

Okay...break time (which has basically been all night) needs to be over now.

Later loves!

Ps. Bookworms cafe serves vanilla chai now? what? since when?  It's not bad...but no comparison to the ones Erika used to make me at Starbucks :)

So my last day of classes has officially been cancelled, due to the lovely and heavy amounts of snow! yay!

but now, I have nothing to do all day, so I am bored!

I had lots of weird dreams last night...

Hope everyone is well!

Later Loves!

it's 8:08 as I write this.

I didn't go to sleep last night and have found that it made me very productive today.

I studied to two exams, was at the gym at 6:00 am sharp, showered, shaved my legs, brushed my teeth, washed my face (separate from shower routine), blow dryed my hair, then semi-styled my hair, e-mailed my mommy...I had half a day while everyone else is still asleep! haha

I'm not tired yet, but my tummy hurts :(

My boobs are really sensitive today...not that any of you needed or cared to know that, but it's bugging me, so I thought I'd share. :)

Not something I wrote, but I thought I'd share

They call it the "Quarter-life Crisis." 
It is when you stop going along with the crowd and start realizing that there are many things about yourself that you didn't know and may not like. 
You start feeling insecure and wonder where you will be in a year or two, but then get scared because you barely know where you are now. 
You start realizing that people are selfish and that, maybe, those friends that you thought you were so close to aren't exactly the greatest people you have ever met, and the people you have lost touch with are some of the most important ones. 
What you don't recognize is that they are realizing that too, and aren't really cold, catty, mean or insincere, but that they are as confused as you. 
You look at your job... and it is not even close to what you thought you would be doing, or maybe you are looking for a job and realizing that you are going to have to start at the bottom and that scares you. 
Your opinions have gotten stronger. You see what others are doing and find yourself judging more than usual because suddenly you realize that you have certain boundaries in your life and are constantly adding things to your list of what is acceptable and what isn't. 
One minute, you are insecure and then the next, secure. 
You laugh and cry with the greatest force of your life. 
You feel alone and scared and confused. 
Suddenly, change is the enemy and you try and cling on to the past with dear life, but soon realize that the past is drifting further and further away, and there is nothing to do but stay where you are or move forward. 
You get your heart broken and wonder how someone you loved could do such damage to you. Or you lie in bed and wonder why you can't meet anyone decent enough that you want to get to know better. Or maybe you love someone but love someone else too and cannot figure out why you are doing this because you know 
that you aren't a bad person. 
One night stands and random hook ups start to look cheap. 
Getting wasted and acting like an idiot don't seem as fun. 
You go through the same emotions and questions over and over, and talk with your 
friends about the same topics because you cannot seem to make a decision. 
You worry about loans, money, the future and making a life for yourself... and while winning the race would be great, right now you'd just like to be a contender! 
What you may not realize is that everyone reading this relates to it. 
We are in our best of times and our worst of times, trying as hard as we can to figure this whole thing out.

He promised to take the rain away

and sure enough, as his plane was touching down on the other side of the country, the sun broke through the clouds here for the first time in over a week.

When I think about it now, I'd rather have him and the rain then to have sunny days without him.

I never knew how much I'd miss the rain

I am at work an hour early because I forgot to buy my bus pass yesterday, so I had to ride in with my mommy today (and she leaves for work at the crack of dawn!).

For those of you who don't know, I am working full time this summer at St. Paul Travelers (it's an insurance company in Hartford).  Allison Keeton (who lives with Netta) works here. I feel so old. I was sitting at my desk at work the other day and I realized that I am working a full time at an 8a.m. to 5p.m. job in an office as an intern.  I get coffee, or some equivalent, everyday on my way in.  I park in a commuter lot and take the bus from Manchester in to Hartford, because I don't want to deal with the traffic and bad drivers.  I don't know why, but it just made me feel old. When did playing dress up in mom's work clothes and make-up become a reality?  I miss those summers that consisted of swimming and freeze tag and capture the flag.  When the biggest worry was whether to bring cherry or lemonade flavored juice boxes to camp.  When forgetting your lunch box or skinning your knee qualified as a crisis situation.  The days when you could just have a lemonade stand if you wanted some money.  Back when car insurance and taxes weren't even part of my vocabulary.  Times when, if you liked a boy, you would chase him around playground and maybe even "marry" him by the swingset. Broken hearts weren't a problem because at that age you could fall out of "love" just as quickly as you snap your fingers.  Back when you playing "he loves me, he loves me not" with a flower was all the proof you needed of a boys affection.

Do you remember those first few glimpses of "freedom"?  like the trip to Washington D.C. There was adult supervision, yes, but there was 300 or so of us and 10(?) of them.  We swore. We stayed up late. We watched HBO...when we definitely shouldn't have. We laughed, we fought, some cried, we sang, we raced...we had a great carefree time.  I miss, all sorts of miss, those days.  

I loved being 10 and 12 and 15 and every year before and inbetween.  Not that I don't like being 19, I just miss the days when things seemed so much simpler.  The funny part is, I know, in 5 years, give or take a few years, I will look back at being 19 and remember it as being a simpler more carefree time. Complications and responsibilities are all a part of growing up I guess.  I just hope that I am always able to take some time to remember what it was like to be young and to enjoy everything around me.
